		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Amanda Rea</span></strong> lives in Madison, Wisconsin, where she&rsquo;s the Carl Djerassi Fiction Fellow at the Institute for Creative Writing. Her work has appeared in <em>Green Mountains Review</em>, <em>Iowa Review</em>, and <em>Indiana Review</em>. Her father, whose songwriting is described in her essay in this issue, will release his second album this summer.</p><a href="/contributors/amanda-rea" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
